modules.description: This module enables input formatting and validation by interfacing with a JavaScript library, offering operations to create specialized formatters for financial, telecommunication, and temporal data entry. It works with JavaScript objects representing Cleave instances, configuration records for format rules, and string-based region codes to handle localized phone number parsing. Typical use cases include enhancing web forms with real-time credit card validation, phone number normalization with region-specific formatting, and date/number entry masking in browser-based OCaml applications.

This module enables input formatting and validation through a JavaScript library, creating specialized formatters for financial, telecommunication, and temporal data. It operates on configuration records, JavaScript Cleave instances, and region codes to support localized phone number parsing and real-time validation. Examples include masking credit card entries, normalizing phone numbers by region, and applying date or number formatting in web forms. Key operations involve instantiating formatters, applying validation rules, and handling input events in browser-based OCaml applications.
